modules.description: This module defines a type `t` representing the SameSite attribute values for HTTP cookies, including `default`, `none`, `lax`, and `strict`. It provides equality and comparison operations, conversion to S-expressions, and serialization to cookie-compatible strings. Use this module when setting or parsing SameSite attributes in HTTP responses or requests.

This module handles parsing, creating, and serializing HTTP cookies according to RFC6265. It supports operations to construct cookies with attributes like domain, path, max-age, and same-site, and to convert cookies to and from header values. It works with strings, timestamps, and optional attributes, enabling concrete use cases like validating incoming cookies, building response cookies, or managing session identifiers with security constraints.
